00:04:56.130 --> 00:04:59.070
as being these early
first steps of AR.

00:04:59.070 --> 00:05:01.650
But if you're a
product person, it's

00:05:01.650 --> 00:05:05.160
not that easy to see how you're
going to create a product out

00:05:05.160 --> 00:05:08.220
of it, unless you're doing
experiential marketing,

00:05:08.220 --> 00:05:10.690
or immersive theater,
or something like that.

00:05:10.690 --> 00:05:13.140
And so if you have to get
people to go to a place

00:05:13.140 --> 00:05:16.200
to experience AR, it's
kind of hard to build

00:05:16.200 --> 00:05:19.620
a scalable product
around it in that sense.

00:05:19.620 --> 00:05:22.160
So there's this next
phase, which was--

00:05:22.160 --> 00:05:23.910
I'm sure many of you
are familiar with it.

00:05:23.910 --> 00:05:25.660
If you're not,
it's sort of where

00:05:25.660 --> 00:05:30.500
we're using images
tracked on mobile devices

00:05:30.500 --> 00:05:31.940
to pin content in the world.

00:05:31.940 --> 00:05:34.730
And the way that worked is
you would have your phone,

00:05:34.730 --> 00:05:37.350
and there would be some
sort of image or QR code.

00:05:37.350 --> 00:05:39.260
And by using that as
a reference point,

00:05:39.260 --> 00:05:41.000
we could put this
digital content

00:05:41.000 --> 00:05:43.310
overlaid into the world.

00:05:43.310 --> 00:05:44.280
And it was awesome.

00:05:44.280 --> 00:05:46.040
It actually represented
this big jump

00:05:46.040 --> 00:05:48.680
because, now, you could
deliver AR experiences

00:05:48.680 --> 00:05:49.910
on mobile devices, right?

00:05:49.910 --> 00:05:51.690
I could put
something on a store.

00:05:51.690 --> 00:05:53.480
Someone could download
it, and then they

00:05:53.480 --> 00:05:56.100
could have this cool experience.

00:05:56.100 --> 00:05:57.970
But there were a
couple of shortcomings.

00:05:57.970 --> 00:06:01.500
The tracking wasn't as
good as what we have now.

00:06:01.500 --> 00:06:04.040
And if you lost sight
of the image marker,

00:06:04.040 --> 00:06:06.050
it would kind of go haywire.

00:06:06.050 --> 00:06:08.960
And most importantly, you
had to have this image

00:06:08.960 --> 00:06:10.495
marker in space, right?

00:06:10.495 --> 00:06:12.120
And that's a really
tricky proposition.

00:06:12.120 --> 00:06:13.860
It's hard enough to get
someone to download an app.

00:06:13.860 --> 00:06:15.350
But to get them
to download an app

00:06:15.350 --> 00:06:18.287
and also print something
out can be challenging.

00:06:18.287 --> 00:06:20.120
And so we did see some
adoption of this tech

00:06:20.120 --> 00:06:22.670
in marketing campaigns, where
there's physical collateral,

00:06:22.670 --> 00:06:24.920
or if there were
instruction booklets,

00:06:24.920 --> 00:06:27.950
things like that, where you
would know that your app could

00:06:27.950 --> 00:06:30.620
have those markers available.

00:06:30.620 --> 00:06:34.760
But the game really changed
with modern AR platforms,

00:06:34.760 --> 00:06:35.960
like ARCore.

00:06:35.960 --> 00:06:39.070
And this was basically,
from a product perspective,

00:06:39.070 --> 00:06:40.160
like a quantum jump.

00:06:40.160 --> 00:06:44.390
I remember when I first
saw these new AR platforms.

00:06:44.390 --> 00:06:46.550
I was working with the
image maker stuff, right?

00:06:46.550 --> 00:06:47.960
And there was always a struggle.

00:06:47.960 --> 00:06:49.340
And I saw some
videos, and I just

00:06:49.340 --> 00:06:52.010
was like, I don't believe that.

00:06:52.010 --> 00:06:52.710
That's not real.

00:06:52.710 --> 00:06:54.860
So I went out, I bought
devices, and I tried it.

00:06:54.860 --> 00:06:56.630
And I remember sitting
there and thinking,

00:06:56.630 --> 00:06:59.510
man, this can actually
be a thing now.

00:06:59.510 --> 00:07:03.860
I can release production quality
user experiences with AR.

00:07:03.860 --> 00:07:06.500
And the really important
thing about this

00:07:06.500 --> 00:07:08.600
is there's no need for markers.

00:07:08.600 --> 00:07:10.910
That is a feature
that you can access,

00:07:10.910 --> 00:07:14.660
but you can send anyone a
link to download your app.

00:07:14.660 --> 00:07:18.570
They can download it, and no
additional effort is required.

00:07:18.570 --> 00:07:20.370
They can have the
experience you intended.

00:07:20.370 --> 00:07:22.100
And so lowering that
barrier to entry,

00:07:22.100 --> 00:07:25.340
combined with a really
consistent output of quality,

00:07:25.340 --> 00:07:31.810
has just really changed the
game for AR in a product sense.

00:07:31.810 --> 00:07:36.010
And that brings us to today,
which is AR as a feature.

00:07:36.010 --> 00:07:39.430
So when these platforms
first hit, everyone went out

00:07:39.430 --> 00:07:41.020
and we were making AR stuff.

00:07:41.020 --> 00:07:43.870
That's when I made an app
you can paint in the air.

00:07:43.870 --> 00:07:46.810
It's really cool, really fun.

00:07:46.810 --> 00:07:48.820
But these were these AR apps.

00:07:48.820 --> 00:07:51.070
And what our team
has discovered,

00:07:51.070 --> 00:07:53.710
because we sort of go around
inside of Google and say,

00:07:53.710 --> 00:07:58.090
how can AR unlock new
potential use cases for people,

00:07:58.090 --> 00:08:00.738
is that your app doesn't
have to be an AR app.

00:08:00.738 --> 00:08:02.530
And in fact, some of
the most powerful ways

00:08:02.530 --> 00:08:05.140
we can execute on AR
is including it just

00:08:05.140 --> 00:08:07.870
as a feature in an existing app.

00:08:07.870 --> 00:08:10.120
And today is the perfect
time to be doing it,

00:08:10.120 --> 00:08:12.720
because these frameworks
make it super easy.

00:08:12.720 --> 00:08:16.630
When you see AR, it can look
kind of like black magic,

00:08:16.630 --> 00:08:17.810
like it's super hard.

00:08:17.810 --> 00:08:20.570
You need to be a mega genius
to get AR stuff happening.

00:08:20.570 --> 00:08:24.070
But, in reality, ARCore
makes it super easy,

00:08:24.070 --> 00:08:25.570
and there are tons
of helpful tools.

00:08:25.570 --> 00:08:28.390
So today is the
time when, I think,

00:08:28.390 --> 00:08:29.980
any product person
can be evaluating

00:08:29.980 --> 00:08:32.380
their product for this stuff.

00:08:32.380 --> 00:08:37.530
So AR as a feature essentially
means that the whole app

00:08:37.530 --> 00:08:38.700
isn't about AR.

00:08:38.700 --> 00:08:42.480
So what you see here
is Google Maps, right?

00:08:42.480 --> 00:08:45.520
And Google Maps
is not an AR app.

00:08:45.520 --> 00:08:47.020
It helps you get
where you're going.

00:08:47.020 --> 00:08:49.440
It helps you search
for awesome stuff,

00:08:49.440 --> 00:08:50.880
but it's not all about AR.

00:08:50.880 --> 00:08:55.470
However, the team discovered
that, for certain areas like,

00:08:55.470 --> 00:08:57.380
in this case,
walking navigation,

00:08:57.380 --> 00:09:00.180
it can be really powerful and
enhance the app experience

00:09:00.180 --> 00:09:02.250
to use AR in those moments.

00:09:02.250 --> 00:09:05.250
And same in your I/O app.

00:09:05.250 --> 00:09:06.750
