and use Signpost,

00:09:06.750 --> 00:09:08.340
you can get where you're going.

00:09:08.340 --> 00:09:13.560
But it's not it's not relegated
just to navigational use cases,

00:09:13.560 --> 00:09:14.770
as we'll see later.

00:09:14.770 --> 00:09:16.650
So I'm going to kick
it over to Diane,

00:09:16.650 --> 00:09:18.720
who's going to tell you
about how you can assess

00:09:18.720 --> 00:09:21.300
the stuff you're working
on to see if maybe AR could

00:09:21.300 --> 00:09:22.857
do something awesome with it.

00:09:22.857 --> 00:09:23.565
DIANE WANG: Cool.

00:09:23.565 --> 00:09:24.810
Thank You, Austin.

00:09:24.810 --> 00:09:27.030
So let's bring it
over to all of you

00:09:27.030 --> 00:09:29.850
and start talking about
how you can determine

00:09:29.850 --> 00:09:32.200
if AR is right for your app.

00:09:32.200 --> 00:09:35.220
Here are several
principles and questions

00:09:35.220 --> 00:09:37.650
that you can ask
yourself as you decide on

00:09:37.650 --> 00:09:42.030
whether AR has the potential to
add a lot of value to your app.

00:09:42.030 --> 00:09:44.100
And this is all going to
be drawn from our team's

00:09:44.100 --> 00:09:48.250
experience, but we'll just kick
it off with the big question.

00:09:48.250 --> 00:09:53.010
So we always start off by asking
ourselves the simple question,

00:09:53.010 --> 00:09:56.040
why do we want to use AR?

00:09:56.040 --> 00:09:59.490
And that really helps
ground us in user value

00:09:59.490 --> 00:10:02.220
and thinking about
the specific value

00:10:02.220 --> 00:10:06.420
that this suite of
technologies brings to us.

00:10:06.420 --> 00:10:09.790
And going a little bit
deeper here, on our team,

00:10:09.790 --> 00:10:13.800
we think that there are two
broad categories of experiences

00:10:13.800 --> 00:10:16.770
that AR can make shine.

00:10:16.770 --> 00:10:19.230
Use these as guidelines,
as starting points,

00:10:19.230 --> 00:10:23.090
to answer this question.

00:10:23.090 --> 00:10:24.640
So here are the two dimensions.

00:10:24.640 --> 00:10:27.370
You may have heard this
in our developer keynote.

00:10:27.370 --> 00:10:30.530
The two dimensions here are
helpfulness and creativity.

00:10:30.530 --> 00:10:32.570
So these are two
broad categories,

00:10:32.570 --> 00:10:34.660
and that's one really
easy way to get

00:10:34.660 --> 00:10:38.440
started in thinking about,
hey, does my app fit in here?

00:10:38.440 --> 00:10:41.110
Does my feature fit in here?

00:10:41.110 --> 00:10:44.230
And just thinking about these
from a broad perspective--

00:10:44.230 --> 00:10:48.370
helpfulness is a really great
place for AR to help shine.

00:10:48.370 --> 00:10:52.360
Because AR understands so
much of the spatial context

00:10:52.360 --> 00:10:54.160
around a user that,
if you're trying

00:10:54.160 --> 00:10:57.190
to have an app that helps the
user accomplish something,

00:10:57.190 --> 00:11:02.150
AR can do that in a lot
more quicker of a way.

00:11:02.150 --> 00:11:04.650
And when you think
about creativity,

00:11:04.650 --> 00:11:08.470
AR has a lot of
opportunity here to help

00:11:08.470 --> 00:11:10.240
make features shine as well.

00:11:10.240 --> 00:11:13.330
You can see that AR allows you
to be a lot more expressive

00:11:13.330 --> 00:11:16.240
and engaging when you're
thinking about a creativity

00:11:16.240 --> 00:11:17.110
feature.

00:11:17.110 --> 00:11:19.690
You can directly overlay
things and output content

00:11:19.690 --> 00:11:23.800
into the world and also
have suggestive content

00:11:23.800 --> 00:11:25.960
that leverages our
understanding of the context.

00:11:28.780 --> 00:11:31.450
But beyond these two
buckets, our team

00:11:31.450 --> 00:11:33.640
also has some other
insights that we found,

00:11:33.640 --> 00:11:37.010
just by working across
a lot of different apps.

00:11:37.010 --> 00:11:39.310
So here's one to start with.

00:11:39.310 --> 00:11:43.000
One area that we found
has high AR potential

00:11:43.000 --> 00:11:45.430
is when there's
information from the world

00:11:45.430 --> 00:11:47.990
that we'd like to
have in our app.

00:11:47.990 --> 00:11:50.210
Often, if users need
to look something up

00:11:50.210 --> 00:11:53.320
from the phone to
complete a flow in an app,

00:11:53.320 --> 00:11:58.320
AR has opportunities to enhance
and streamline that experience.

00:11:58.320 --> 00:12:01.710
AR has the ability to capture
information from the world

00:12:01.710 --> 00:12:06.010
and make user journeys a lot
easier and more streamlined.

00:12:06.010 --> 00:12:08.230
So that was from the
helpfulness dimension.

00:12:08.230 --> 00:12:11.310
But when you're thinking
about creativity apps as well,

00:12:11.310 --> 00:12:13.260
AR can suggest
expressive content

00:12:13.260 --> 00:12:15.475
that's relevant to
the scene and context.

00:12:19.760 --> 00:12:21.710
And another category
of experiences

00:12:21.710 --> 00:12:25.100
that has high opportunity
for AR features

00:12:25.100 --> 00:12:27.320
is when someone needs to
interact with the real world

00:12:27.320 --> 00:12:28.770
to use our app.

00:12:28.770 --> 00:12:30.770
So if someone needs to
do something in real life

00:12:30.770 --> 00:12:33.380
to complete a flow, these
are really great signs

00:12:33.380 --> 00:12:35.850
that AR may be useful.

